page.title: 10Flora/Fauna in Rathmell NW
page.content: There are numerous varieties of flowers, trees, animals and birds. Most of the{flowers}are common ones, but there are scores of varieties in the hedgerows to the east and on the{heathland}to the west. There are several wooded areas, some quite dense.{Deciduous trees predominate but there are{coniferous {woods}too. These trees grow in the valleys of the becks and are most numerous in the eastern part of the block. The trees in the western part are more isolated and grow mainly by farmhouses to give them some protection. The{birds}vary from crows, starlings and blackbirds to pheasant and partridge. There are also many {wild animals}including badgers, hares, foxes and rabbits.
